Cholera - Sri Lanka (04) 980814215639
Cholera - Sri Lanka (05) 980909004714
Date: Fri, 11 Sep 1998 15:39:07 -0500
Source: Daily News - LakeHouse, 11 Sep 1998
Via: Clyde Markon <docmarkon@worldnet.att.net>

Twenty-seven cases of cholera have been reported from four villages in the
Welikanda police area in the North Central - Polonnaruwa district, reports
the Lankapuvath Correspondent in the province. According to the police,
the patients from Mahasenpura, Malwila, Katuwanwila and the Ethugala
refugee camps are now receiving treatment at the Welikanda hospital.
